---
title: Polenta With Zucchini & Carrot Ragù plus Toasted Ciabatta Points & Parmesan
description: Creamy polenta and ragù are a classic pairing you can make extra-fast! Heat our precooked polenta, then swirl in sour cream, cream cheese, Parmesan, and butter for a luxuriously rich texture. Top it with a hearty tomato ragù packed with zucchini, onion, and carrots, and serve crisp ciabatta toasts alongside, ready to scoop it all up.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66ba340afb4859096c8b61c4-df284012.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66ba340afb4859096c8b61c4-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/polenta-with-zucchini-carrot-ragu-66ba340afb4859096c8b61c4
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Eastern European
time required: 20 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 14 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1790 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick
pieces. Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1%unit} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Trim
and halve @zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise; cut crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick
half-moons.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add carrots, onion, and zucchini; season with @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
@Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}(half the Italian Seasoning), @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and lightly
browned, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @water{1/4%cup}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add @precooked polenta{8.8%ounce}
and @water{1/3%cup}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Whisk in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @cream cheese{2%tablespoon},
@Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, and @butter{1%tablespoon}; cook, whisking
occasionally, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and
pepper if desired. (If polenta seems too thick, add water 1 TBSP at a time
until it reaches desired consistency.)

Meanwhile, halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1%unit}.

Cut ciabatta on a diagonal into triangles and drizzle with @olive oil{1%teaspoon}.

Divide polenta and ragù between #shallow bowls{} in separate sections. Serve
ciabatta on the side.

> Creamy polenta and ragù are a classic pairing you can make extra-fast! Swirl in sour cream,
> cream cheese, Parmesan, and butter for a luxuriously rich texture. Top it with a hearty tomato
> ragù packed with zucchini, onion, and carrots, and serve crisp ciabatta toasts alongside, ready
> to scoop it all up.